  %section
    %h1 About Squidtree
    %p Squidtree was developed to showcase design and technical prowess, but also to provide a proving ground for experimental ideas and new development techniques. Its current design features a dynamic color scheme based on the progress of time (inspired by Shaun Inman). Overt ime, the colors fade through seasonal colors&em;a blog post made in spring will keep its green shade, while a visitor in October will find the site transitioning from summer's orange to winter's blue. It also employs a responsive design with retina graphics to benefit mobile users. It is openly developed and its source code can be found over at GitHub.
    %p Under the hood, it's running Rails with a MongoDB database.

